The paper deals with sentiment analysis, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of a convolutional neural network (CNN) for sentiment analysis suggests that the paper may also fall under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves identifying key words, which could fall under the sub-category of information retrieval (cs.IR) or computer vision (cs.CV) if the words are being identified visually.
